cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach to unsupervised embedding learning for image classification tasks. This involves developing a unique set of losses that can gather similar samples nearby within a low-density space while keeping invariant features intact against data augmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
